      <section id="introduction">
        <h1 class="section-header">Getting Started</h1>
        <p>
          The web console allows authenticated users to
          <ul>
            <li>Configure and view environments i.e. virtual private clouds and subnets.</li>
            <li>Launch and view virtual servers (Amazon EC2 instances).</li>
            <li>User can specify different configurations for instances like the subnet, security
              groups and key-pair to use.</li>
              <li>The users can also start, stop and terminate the instances.</li>
              <li>The user can also contact the admin for queries.</li>
          </ul>
          <h3>Running locally</h3>
          To use this console on local development server. Follow these steps-: 
          <ol>
            <li>Clone the github repo 
              <code>git clone "repo name"</code>
            </li>
            <li>Install NPM packages 
              <code>npm install</code>
            </li>
            <li>Start on port localhost:3000 
              <code>npm start</code>
            </li>
          </ol>
          <h3>Running on EC2 instance</h3>
            <ol>
              <li>
                Create an EC2 instance. Enable auto-assign public IP.
              </li>
              <li>
                In security groups enable custom TCP incoming from anywhere for port 3000.
              </li>
              <li>Connect to your Linux instance as ec2-user using SSH.
              </li>
              <li>
                <code>sudo yum -y install curl</code>
                <code> -sL https://rpm.nodesource.com/setup_14.x | sudo bash -</code>
              </li>
              <li>
                Clone github repo
                <code>git clone "repo-name"</code>
              </li>
              <li>
                Install dependencies
                <code>npm install</code>
              </li>
              <li>
                Start the server
                <code>npm start</code>
                Now copy and paste the public Ipv4 DNS and add :3000 at the end
              </li>

            </ol>
        </p>
